Body: Description: Hi Team, I worked with a member of support at the beginning this month to address a false positive my users were receiving. We had set up the website segaldev.crm.dynamics.com* to be on the allow list. Despite that, they are still getting these notifications. Can you advise how we can fix this on our instance please?

Invitation updated. Attendees: Iosif Muntean, Anoush d'Orville
What We've Learned Updated: We have scheduled a remote session for tomorrow(25.02.2025 22:30 RO time)
Next Steps Updated: Investigate the issue during the remote session.

What We've Learned Updated: We have scheduled a remote session for tomorrow(25.02.2025 22:30 RO time)

During today's meeting, we discussed the CAP - Deep Packet Inspection (Policy Allowlist) and Regular Expression(Policy Denylist) - where and how to use them.

What We've Learned Updated: We have scheduled a remote session for tomorrow(25.02.2025 22:30 RO time)

During today's meeting, we discussed the CAP - Deep Packet Inspection (Policy Allowlist) and Regular Expression(Policy Denylist) - where and how to use them.

The customer reopened the ticket and we scheduled a remote session in which we added more options to the Allowlist dictionary and also performed an EPP server upgrade + started the EPP client software upgrade job.
